⃝
Density functional calculations, Dispersion, DNA quartets, Hydrogen bonding, π–Stacking

In this presentation, I discuss the performance of various types of density functionals (GGA, dispersioncorrected, hybrid) for describing the hydrogen bonds and the stacking interactions in DNA base dimers, using the
ADF code [1]. Comparison with ab initio benchmark data shows that dispersion-corrected functionals perform well
whereas B3LYP fails completely, especially for stacked systems [2-4].

Fig. 1. Ditopic receptor G4NaClA4 in aqueous solution: top view (left) and side view (right).

