Next, I address the question why adenine has to be sandwiched between guanine quartets in order to form planar
adenine quartets. Furthermore, the stacking complex of a guanine and an adenine quartet, G4A4, is proposed as a
potent ditopic receptor for table salt in aqueous solution (see Fig. 1) [4].
